[h1]GK Raiding Expanded[/h1]

Steal their people. Strip their planets. Fund your own pirate enclave.

[b]Stellaris 4.2.3 | Compatible with 4.3 beta[/b]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Pop Raiding Rework[/h2]

Five war goals let you tailor exactly how you take what you want. Capture pops, liberate the enslaved, free machines, strip planets of resources, or reap entire civilizations in a total war with no surrender and no cap. Two policies give finer control over your raiding focus and whether your forces target organics, machines, or both.

[h2]New Pillaging System[/h2]

Every burst of devastation strips a planet of what it actually produces. Bombardment bleeds them dry over time, invasion cashes out what's left, and a Pillage war forces surviving colonies to pay tribute on surrender. Trade is especially valuable as plunder, and research converts into consumer goods your economy can use.

[h2]Civics[/h2]

Seven new civics bring raiding to every empire type.

[b]Emancipators[/b] and [b]Liberation Enterprise[/b] wage war to free the enslaved. [b]Robo-Liberators[/b], [b]Synthetic Liberation Corp[/b], and [b]Freedom Directive[/b] do the same for machines under organic rule. [b]Harvest Incorporated[/b] treats conquered populations as corporate assets. [b]Harvesting Protocol[/b] abducts organics to feed a machine intelligence's power grid, starting with its own battery species.

[h2]Despoliation Traditions[/h2]

Any empire can walk the path of plunder. Adopting the Despoliation tree unlocks resource pillaging and the Pillage war goal. Completing the tree grants an Ascension Perk slot and unlocks the Privateer Enclave.

[h2]Privateer Enclave[/h2]

Found your own pirate haven. It raids autonomously, shakes down its victims for tribute, and pays you dividends. Its salvager crews pick through the wreckage of battle for alloys, minerals, and rare materials. Upgrade it to expand its fleet, increase raid frequency, and unlock richer payouts. Each enclave develops its own personality at founding. Build a Smuggler's Port on your starbases for additional trade value.

[hr][/hr]

[h3]DLC Support[/h3]

Most core features function without DLCs.
They are required for the following additional features:
[list]
[*][b]Overlord[/b]: Privateer Enclave
[*][b]Grand Archive[/b]: Enclave specimens and Boarding Cables tradition variant
[*][b]Paragon[/b]: Recovery Fleets council agenda
[/list]

[h3]Compatibility[/h3]

Should be compatible with most mods. Full overwrites:
[list]
[*]Bombardment stance: [i]raiding[/i]
[*]War goals: [i]wg_plunder[/i], [i]wg_plunder_raid[/i]
[*]Casus belli: [i]cb_despoliation[/i], [i]cb_pirate_raid[/i]
[*]Game rules: [i]can_orbital_bombard[/i], [i]can_spawn_debris[/i]
[*]Scripted triggers: [i]is_unfriendly[/i], [i]is_slaver[/i], [i]prefers_commander_governors[/i], [i]has_murderous_civic_or_origin[/i]
[*]Policies: [i]debris[/i]
[*]Economic categories: [i]planet_livestock_farmers[/i], [i]planet_livestock_miners[/i], [i]planet_livestock_metallurgists[/i], [i]pop_category_purge[/i], [i]planet_organic_batteries[/i]
[*]Events: [i]enclave.2[/i]
[/list]

